{"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0,"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[],"authorship_tag":"ABX9TyO9vVQ3AtkcBJgGTGEYEz8n"},"kernelspec":{"name":"python3","display_name":"Python 3"},"language_info":{"name":"python"}},"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["* Sistemas de ecuacionnes 1er grado:\n","\n","$AX^T=b$\n","\n","\n","Un sistema de ecuaciones esta defindo por:\n","\n","a₁₁x₁ + a₁₂x₂ + a₁₃x₃ + ... + a₁ₙxₙ = b₁\n","\n","a₂₁x₁ + a₂₂x₂ + a₂₃x₃ + ... + a₂ₙxₙ = b₂\n","\n","a₃₁x₁ + a₃₂x₂ + a₃₃x₃ + ... + a₃ₙxₙ = b₃\n","\n","...\n","\n","aₘ₁x₁ + aₘ₂x₂ + aₘ₃x₃ + ... + aₘₙxₙ = bₘ\n","\n","Donde $a_{ij}$ se llaman coeficientes siendo:\n","\n","$i=1,2,3,.......,n$\n","\n","$j=1,2,3,.......,m$\n","\n","* Teorema:\n","1. Sea m<n, entonces el sistema homogeneo $AX^T=0$ tiene al menos una solucion.\n","2. Sea m<n, entonces el sistema homogeneo $AX^T=b$ tiene infinitas soluciones o ninguna solucion.\n","\n","* Metodos para resolver sistemas ecuaciones lineales:\n","\n","1. Metodo de cramer:\n","\n","Dado el sistema de ecuaciones:\n","\n","a₁₁x₁ + a₁₂x₂ + ... + a₁ₙxₙ = b₁\n","\n","a₂₁x₁ + a₂₂x₂ + ... + a₂ₙxₙ = b₂\n","\n","...\n","\n","aₙ₁x₁ + aₙ₂x₂ + ... + aₙₙxₙ = bₙ\n","\n","Se calcula el determinante principal D de los coeficientes de las incógnitas:\n","\n","D =\n","\n","    | a₁₁  a₁₂  ...  a₁ₙ |\n","\n","    | a₂₁  a₂₂  ...  a₂ₙ |\n","\n","    | ...         ...    |\n","\n","    | aₙ₁  aₙ₂  ...  aₙₙ |\n","\n","Se calcula los determinantes Dx₁, Dx₂, ..., Dxₙ, donde Dxᵢ que se obtiene al reemplazar la columna i-esima de D por los términos independientes b₁, b₂, ..., bₙ:\n","\n","Dx₁ =\n","\n","    |b₁  a₁₂  ...  a₁ₙ |\n","\n","    | b₂  a₂₂  ...  a₂ₙ |\n","\n","    | ...         ...   |\n","\n","    | bₙ  aₙ₂  ...  aₙₙ |\n","\n","Y se calcula las soluciones x₁, x₂, ..., xₙ dividiendo cada determinante Dxᵢ por el determinante principal D:\n","\n","x₁ = Dx₁ / D\n","\n","x₂ = Dx₂ / D\n","\n","...\n","\n","xₙ = Dxₙ / D\n"],"metadata":{"id":"gdXCo60Zm5g5"}}]}